SIMPLE: shaving
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Shaving
<hw>Shav"ing</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The act of one who, or
that which, shaves; specifically, the act of cutting off the beard with
a razor.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>That which is shaved off; a thin slice or strip
pared off with a shave, a knife, a plane, or other cutting
instrument.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧<xex>Shaving</xex> of silver.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Chaucer.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Shaving brush</b></col>, <cd>a brush used in lathering
the face preparatory to shaving it.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Shaw</ent>⟦br⟧
